#!usr/bin/perl -w

use Pod::Pdf;
pod2pdf(@ARGV);
exit 0;

__END__

=head1 NAME

pod2pdf - Interface file for F<Pod.pm>

=head1 SYNOPSIS

From the shell enter any of the following examples:


	$ pod2pdf --verbose 1 --paper usletter <file>
	$ pod2pdf -verbose 1 -paper usletter <file>
	$ pod2pdf -v 2 -pa letter <file>
	$ cat <file> | pod2pdf
	
NB F<Pdf.pm> will only process B<single> files

=head1 DESCRIPTION

F<pod2pdf> provides a simple interface to allow the module F<Pdf.pm> to be called from a shell prompt.

=head1 SEE ALSO

F<Pdf.pm>

